e by considering its polyfunctionality. At the same time that it presents a state-of-the-art analysis of the shrine of Dodona and contributes with a new theory concerning the function of some structures located in the sacred area, it also highlights the close connection between a settlement and its region. For this reason, the aim is to become a reference work that allows continuing the current trend of studies focused on Epirus, a territory traditionally considered as secondary.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 4aDodona. 4aEpirus. 4aOrakel. 4aPilgerschaft. 7aRELIGION / History.2bisacsh  aDodona.  aEpirus.  aoracles.  apilgrimage.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2021z978311075072008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021 Englishz978311075405608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021z97831107538130 cEPUBz97831107277220 cprintz978311072751740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311072759340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110727593423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110727593.jpg  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Ebook Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075072-0  DG Ebook Package English 2021b2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  a978-3-11-075381-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075405-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Classical Studies 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKAL